history.content:
FEMTech Launch is a program that provides office hours, extra help, and tutoring sessions specifically geared towards underrepresented minorities in lower level CS courses: 61A, 61B, 70, and Data 8. If you are interested in being a part of a section for any of these classes, you can find the interest form and more information here: tinyurl.com/sp21launchstudent.

We're also looking for motivated, passionate people that are interested in teaching and guiding less experienced students in these lower division CS classes. You will be working in a team of 2 tutors focused on helping 3-5 students, as well as providing additional support to your students. If you would be interested in being a tutor, you can find the application and more information here: tinyurl.com/sp21launchtutor.

Thank you!
history.subject: FEMTech Launch Tutoring for CS 61A, CS 61B, CS 70, and Data 8
